21:04.810 --> 21:07.554
This in itself is an act of grace.

21:08.275 --> 21:14.023
God's command, God's word, God's guidance for them because the Lord is their healer.

21:16.627 --> 21:19.090
Well, the Lord too is our healer.

21:20.578 --> 21:25.104
And we see this most clearly, of course, in the person of Jesus Christ.

21:26.285 --> 21:40.923
Jesus Christ, the great physician who heals our infirmities, who meets us in our disease and takes care of us, who takes care of our diseases as the prophet Isaiah says.

21:41.424 --> 21:45.989
The Lord who comes to call not the righteous, but the sinner.

21:46.029 --> 21:49.874
The Lord who comes not to call the healthy, but the

21:50.818 --> 21:56.046
But the sick, Jesus Christ is our healer.

21:57.127 --> 21:59.951
We see it most clearly in what he does.

22:00.031 --> 22:02.295
Remember, Jesus Christ, he heals physically.

22:02.355 --> 22:03.837
He heals people's lamest.

22:04.238 --> 22:05.860
He calls the lame person to walk.

22:06.120 --> 22:09.866
He heals those that have an uncontrolled bleeding.

22:10.146 --> 22:10.987
He heals those.

22:11.288 --> 22:12.850
He gives sight to

22:12.962 --> 22:14.705
He gives sight to the blind.

22:14.725 --> 22:16.628
He cures skin diseases.

22:17.108 --> 22:19.071
Jesus Christ, he casts out demons.

22:19.492 --> 22:25.521
Jesus Christ heals the relationship that we have with the Father because on the cross, he sheds his blood.

22:25.561 --> 22:28.786
Jesus Christ, he drinks this bitter cup of God's wrath.

22:28.806 --> 22:36.077
He drinks this bitter cup of sin and death so that we might know healing, so that we might know restoration.

22:38.380 --> 22:39.442
Jesus Christ,

22:40.194 --> 22:52.289
Symbolically, we can look back and read this passage and say, well, just as the waters were healed by this piece of wood, by this tree, now the Lord enters into our hearts.

22:52.309 --> 22:55.974
He enters into our bitter soul, our bitter heart and our bitter life.

22:56.314 --> 22:57.496
And He makes us sweet.

22:58.156 --> 22:59.198
He makes us clean.

22:59.238 --> 23:01.481
He makes us pleasing to the Lord.

23:02.802 --> 23:06.066
And so we know now that God indeed is our healer.

23:06.667 --> 23:09.010
God is our physical healer.

23:09.954 --> 23:21.672
We had an Oasis group this past week and I was reminded, I was able to retell a story of how God healed me from a brain abscess that I had when I was eight years old.

23:22.693 --> 23:36.434
How many of you have experienced the healing touch of a doctor, of a nurse, of a surgeon when they administer antibiotics or when they cast a broken bone or when they replace a failing joint?

23:36.994 --> 23:42.202
their skill, their ability comes from the hand of the Lord's provision.

23:43.103 --> 23:59.887
Well, how many times have we been sick, laid up in bed for a day or several days, unable to get out of bed, and that we're finally able to get back up again, and the great preacher Charles Spurgeon, he likens this to like a mini resurrection, where we are brought from death to life.

24:01.049 --> 24:04.434
This is the Lord's design where he equips,

24:04.802 --> 24:07.606
builds us, he designs us to fight off infection.

24:08.767 --> 24:17.099
Even in our health, even when health is good, this comes at the hand of the Lord, who is our healer, the Lord, who is our protector.

24:18.501 --> 24:30.477
Now, the number of times that we are sick, number of times that we are sick, it's number of times we can look to say, oh, God has healed us.

24:30.898 --> 24:32.320
God has made us well again.

24:32.380 --> 24:34.162
God has protected us.

24:34.402 --> 24:35.404
But we do suffer, right?

24:35.664 --> 24:36.506
We do get sick.

24:37.347 --> 24:43.719
And sometimes the Lord does deem it necessary that we suffer, but when we suffer, we are led close to Him.

24:43.940 --> 24:53.938
As the song said, we are assured that whenever we walk through this red sea road that we never walk alone, that the Lord brings us to these places of ultimate healing.

24:54.754 --> 24:58.221
I was talking to one of our members, Kay, Kay Bolander.

24:58.241 --> 25:00.845
I got her permission to share this with you all.

25:01.206 --> 25:02.789
I was talking to her this past week.

25:03.009 --> 25:13.970
And so for the last around four years, she's been suffering from liver trouble, where fluid will drain into her abdomen.

25:14.050 --> 25:34.736
It's essentially, it's gonna bring her to the end of her life, which she's talked about, but she'll be the first person to look back and say, yes, that these years, these years have led me closer to the Lord, that although the Lord has not healed me of this, that the Lord has drawn me closer into fellowship with Him.

25:35.617 --> 25:37.960
And she says, there's times, and she says, Lord, I'm ready.

25:38.901 --> 25:40.543
Lord, I am ready for you to take me.

25:41.424 --> 25:42.866
How can somebody say that?

25:43.842 --> 25:48.787
unless they know that something better is coming, unless they know that there is healing up ahead.

25:49.507 --> 26:00.017
For somebody who has an incurable issue, they know they're maybe going to be passing in the next month, or maybe they're going to die in the next year.

26:00.077 --> 26:05.663
The only way to say that is to know there are these springs on the other side.

26:05.703 --> 26:11.989
The foretaste of what we have now is going to be brought fully, and we enter into the next life.

26:12.049 --> 26:13.490
God is our healer.

26:13.794 --> 26:15.376
God is our healer physically.

26:16.738 --> 26:20.623
But God is also our healer emotionally and spiritually.

26:22.806 --> 26:31.557
But we often don't experience this until we are made to taste the bitter waters from which we are trying to drink.

26:31.577 --> 26:35.442
Right before the Lord heals the waters of Mara,

26:36.290 --> 26:38.473
The people taste its bitterness.

26:38.553 --> 26:43.400
The people have to come to terms after journeying for three days.

26:43.861 --> 26:45.724
Now they taste it and they spit it out.

26:45.764 --> 26:47.066
It's gross, right?

26:48.988 --> 26:50.631
Well, this is the same with us.

26:51.432 --> 27:03.890
Before we are led to the healing of the Lord, the Lord often leads us to this place where we come to see deeply our own bitterness, our own brokenness, our own need for healing.

27:04.546 --> 27:17.059
We're brought to a place where we see just how gross our actions and our words are to God and to other people, how repungent our sin is to the Lord.

27:17.359 --> 27:24.226
The Lord brings us to a place where we're able to see just how much we complain against Him, how much we grumble against Him.

27:24.626 --> 27:32.114
The Lord brings us to a place where we're able to see just how little we can do to heal ourselves.

27:33.762 --> 27:45.758
The amount, the ability of Israel to cast something, to heal this waters by themselves is about our ability to heal our own souls.

27:46.679 --> 27:48.922
We are pointed to Jesus Christ.

27:50.003 --> 27:58.074
We are made to call out to our intercessor, Jesus Christ, the one who heals us physically, mentally and spiritually.

27:59.997 --> 28:00.978
So as we begin,

28:01.474 --> 28:02.275
in this new year.

28:02.376 --> 28:06.824
As we begin as God's broken people saved by grace, this is where we turn.

28:07.445 --> 28:10.350
This is where we have been given grace.

28:10.931 --> 28:13.656
We are led to the grace of God's healing.

28:14.217 --> 28:16.862
We are led to God's restoration.

28:17.463 --> 28:23.353
We are led to find it in Yahweh Rafah, the great physician of Jesus Christ, our Lord.

28:23.834 --> 28:26.098
All of God's people said, amen.

28:38.594 --> 28:41.458
Grace, grace, grace, grace.

28:49.591 --> 28:51.854
I want you to hear the word.

28:51.894 --> 28:53.878
I want you to hear every sermon that I preach.

28:54.659 --> 28:59.466
Hopefully I do the job of communicating God's grace.

29:00.608 --> 29:04.594
God's unmerited favor for his people through Jesus Christ.

29:06.306 --> 29:11.511
I don't want you ever leaving here feeling as if it is a burden to be one of God's people.

29:12.272 --> 29:19.460
I want you to feel as if a burden has been lifted off, that we come to God with nothing and He gives us everything.

29:20.881 --> 29:22.443
Grace is what I want to leave us with.

29:25.065 --> 29:33.554
And as Israel has gone through the Red Sea and as they receive God's instruction, they're expected to respond.

29:34.018 --> 29:36.803
Also in God's grace, they are given response.

29:37.645 --> 29:42.073
And so I like to take this time for us to respond to God's grace.

29:42.895 --> 29:48.064
For us to consider, well, where is God calling me to take action, maybe to change attitude?

29:48.726 --> 29:53.735
Where is God calling me to have my life transformed by the power of his spirit?

29:54.817 --> 29:57.522
So is there something in your life right now that is bitter?

29:58.210 --> 29:59.431
Is it an attitude?

29:59.491 --> 30:00.533
Is it a habit?

30:00.633 --> 30:01.834
Is it words we've said?

30:02.515 --> 30:06.760
Is the Lord opening your eyes somewhere to the bitterness of something in your life?

30:07.300 --> 30:11.044
So that you will repent, so that you will cry out to Him, so that you will look to Him for your healing.

30:12.666 --> 30:15.209
Where do you need the healing of Yahweh, Rafah?

30:15.730 --> 30:16.811
Do you need it in your body?

30:16.831 --> 30:18.152
Do you need it in your mind?

30:18.172 --> 30:19.654
Do you need it in your spirit?

30:21.436 --> 30:26.962
Have you been suffering for a while and the Lord's answer to your prayer has been not yet, my child?

30:29.250 --> 30:30.434
Can you offer your trust?

30:30.835 --> 30:34.084
Can you offer your obedience to the Lord even in this?

30:34.105 --> 30:41.467
I want you to take a minute or two and consider, where is the Lord calling me to respond to His grace?

30:41.547 --> 30:43.954
Yahweh, Raffa, the Lord, our healer.

